Step 1: Set the radius and the height
Step 2: Set the center of the circle
Please make sure the surrounding area is open and free of obstacles before use.\r\n\r\nPlease ensure the drone outdoor and the GPS locked before use.
Fly the drone in front of yourself, make the camera facing you, and adjust the drone\'s height H and distance R(R＞3m). The height and the distance will be the height and the radius in orbit.

Select yourself as target by drawing a frame on the screen. The drone will automatically lock the target to be the center of the orbit circle. Click the frame again for the drone to detect the distance. After the detecting, you can start to orbit.

Click the \"CCW\" or the \"CW\" button, and the drone will fly around the center point. It will stop upon orbiting 360° or you click the button again. Tapping the red button at the bottom of the screen will exit the orbit feature.
Step 1: Set the center of the circle
Step 2: Set the radius and the altitude
Please use the feature in outdoor open area free of obatacles. And ensure the GPS satellites are locked.
Fly the drone to the point you wish to fly around, and adjust the height. Tap the \"Orbit\" in the popup menu in the bottom left corner. The point will be the center point of the orbit.

Tap on "Next". Drag the icon of drone in the lower left corner to the blue area. The horizontal edge shows the radius of the orbit which equals the distance from the center of the circle, the vertical edge shows the altitude relative to the ground. The drone will fly to the point you drag it to. Then tap on \"Start\".

Click the \"CCW\" or the \"CW\" button, and the drone will fly around the center point. It will stop upon orbiting 360° or you click the button again. Tapping the red button at the bottom of the screen will exit the orbit feature.
